name: Gabriel Garbow
bio: From Minnesota; living in California with my husband and corgi.

social_posts.post_text:
NorCal- See this watercolor, “Apotheosis” and more at @kanekogallery in Sacramento through Dec 15. 
.
My solo exhibition “Wreckage and Reveries” includes over a dozen all-new large-scale watercolors. Consider donating to the gallery this holiday season… it provides a wonderful resource for the students at American River College as well as working artists like myself. Contact me for details or to purchase.
.
“Apotheosis” - 22x30” original watercolor by Gabriel Garbow, 2022. Matted and framed to 27.5x35.5”
null

“The Choice is Yours” from the exhibition “Wreckage and Reveries”. The show ends tonight at Kaneko Gallery in Sacramento, CA. 
.
Contact me for purchase info.
.
“The Choice is Yours” - 14x22” original watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022.

I’m back with some new paintings for y’all - available now in my online shop (www.gabrielgarbow.com). Just some fun and simple 8x10s with those classic summer vibes.
.
“Boy with White T-shirt” - 8x10” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
“Man with Red Hawaiian Shorts” - 8x10” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023

“Celebrate Art with Pride!” er … “Celebrate Pride with Art!”
However you want to think about it, my artwork will be enlivening Claudia Castillo Studios gallery for Pride month. Support this Florida-based LGBTQ+ business (and me) by shopping online or in person this month.  I couldn’t be prouder of these paintings. 
.
(Direct links to shops in profile.)

This bright and airy beauty titled “Sunny Side” sold recently through Claudia Castillo gallery. See all the pieces in my current show that are still available by clicking the link in my profile.
.
I find the process of painting the ripples in pool water to be mesmerizing. Throw on a bit of music, and mix a big puddle of blue watercolor paint … the recipe for a good evening!

“Up the Beach” - 16x20” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022. Available for purchase via Claudia Castillo Studios (link in my profile).
.
Named after a song by Jane’s Addiction, it was by accident that the ‘star’ of this piece came out resembling Timothée Chalamet. Protected by an alcove of rock, the subject gazes wistfully into the distance, peacefully detached from the rest of the world.
“Drained” - 16x20” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022. Available via Claudia Castillo Studio. Link in profile.

*** Limited Time ***

Order through July 16 - 11x14” giclee print of “As the Tide Rolls In” for $65 - exclusively via my website through July 16.

An active link to gabrielgarbow.com is in my profile.

I love the vibes of this piece and the subtle colorations of the sand, surf and skin. The original watercolor (sold) has been reformatted from the high resolution scan for the 11x14” size. The scene is reminiscent of sunny mornings in Puerto Vallarta, where I am staying throughout the month. It’s been a great time for me to breathe a little and focus on painting… and soak up some inspiration 🧡

“Barred” - 16x20” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022.
.
Feels like stepping into the sky 
.
Contact @claudiacastillo_artstudio_2215 for purchasing information.

“Silver Cross” - 14x20” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022.
.
Contact @claudiacastillo_artstudio_2215 to purchase.
“Construction Time Again (after Ryan Glista)” - 16x22” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022. Inspired by photo by: @boysbyryan3

“Rocky” - 8x10” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
.
Contact me or purchase via my shop at gabrielgarbow.com

“Swim Good” - 22x30” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow.
.
This one sold already, but let me know if you’d like want a painting like this one for yourself. It would be fun to paddle down this road again.

“Umbrella and Bottled Water” - 14x20” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
.

“Catch the Light” - 14x20” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022. Sold.
.
For more like this, contact me or browse the shop via my website, gabrielgarbow.com
.
It was fun to take the background in a somewhat more abstract direction.  I think it still reads as water and shadows, but it it allows the focus to stay on the foreground and gives an almost cinematic depth-of-field.

“An Underwater Thing I” - 11x14” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
.
Something a little different. Inspired by one of @raviley ‘s recent excursions to the Caribbean. Purchase via my website: gabrielgarbow.com. An active link is in my profile.
.
Also, let me know in the comments if you recognize the song lyric that the title is taken from. It’s a somewhat obscure swipe.

“Sweet Surrender” - 22x30” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2022. Sold.
.
This one was a real achievement. It is my first composition painted on a full sheet of watercolor paper, although a few have come close. It incorporates elements from a half dozen different references - both existing ones and others that I had to stage just for the piece. It was encouraging that a collector had enough faith to commit to a purchase before it was finished. The title comes from a Sarah McLachlan song. Enjoy

The artist and his family. 
.
That’s Ronley holding Biko. In my arms is Biko’s friend Jasper, who is a frequent houseguest.
.
Photo staged and edited by @raviley . Photo taken by an anonymous tourist.

“Green Drawstring” - 8x10” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
.
Painted in Puerto Vallarta. This painting sold shortly after posting, but many other watercolors are available in my online shop at gabrielgarbowart.com

“Green River” - 8x10” original watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
.
A simple and serene painting of a friend in a slightly different style. Click the second link in my profile to purchase via my online shop.

“Boy on Rock (after Tuke)” - 9x12” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023. Sold.
.
Another Puerto Vallarta painting; this one was a chance to try out a different technique involving dryer brushwork and less blending. The piece was inspired by a lovely painting by Henry Scott Tuke. Check out other pieces available to purchase via my online shop: gabrielgarbowart.com/shop

“Triplicate” - 16x20” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023. Sold.
.
One of the paintings started and finished in Puerto Vallarta last month. Triplicate is a continuation or most recent permutation of the “It’s Complicated” series. It turned out so well that it sold to a buyer who viewed it before it was even done. Check out my online shop www.gabrielgarbowart.com/shop for the latest offerings before your favorite piece is sold.

“Donte in Doorway” - 9x14” watercolor on paper, 2023. Sold.
.
Really pleased with how this painting retains an airy feel, even in the rich skin tones. This piece sold to someone who gets my newsletter - recipients got an early look before it was posted to Instagram.
.
Newsletter signup is on the homepage of gabrielgarbowart.com. See what other art is available in my shop - gabrielgarbowart.com/shop.

“Green Drawstring II” - 8x10” watercolor on paper, 2023.
.
A companion piece to the previously posted painting. Available for purchase at the time of posting via gabrielgarbowart.com/shop.

“Green Drawstring III” - 8x10” watercolor on paper, 2023.
.
A slightly different take on the subject. There’s so much that turned out the way I wanted in this piece, I don’t know where to start. The rich shadows that were achieved with a minimum of paint layers is perhaps my proudest accomplishment in this guy.
.
Available to purchase via gabrielgarbowart.com/shop at the time of this posting.

“Green Drawstring IV” - 8x10” watercolor on paper, 2023.
.
The last in this batch. Despite the obvious consistency of the subject matter in many of my paintings, each one tends to tackle some new challenge in terms of technique. It’s a very useful thing for artists to sometimes cement their recent insights through repetition.  That said, these kinds of paintings never feel repetitive, to me.
.
Available to purchase at the time of this posting via gabrielgarbowart.com/shop. Active link in profile.

“Torso (Ronley)” - 8x10” watercolor on paper, 2023.
.
A recent revisit of a pose that rendered a successful painting previously. This time, my husband, @raviley served as the model.
.
Available to purchase via my shop (gabrielgarbowart.com/shop) at the time of this posting

“Snail” - 11x14” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
.
I had a good time painting lily pads previously, so it was about time to try it again.  A different vantage point, and a different, um… co-star are the highlights of this new painting.
.
It is available to purchase, at the time of posting via gabrielgarbowart.com/shop - a clickable link can be found in my profile.

“Travel” - 11x14” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.
.
The latest piece to be completed means to convey the feeling of being pulled away from life’s mundane pressures into an alluring unknown.
.
Sold.  See what else is available to purchase via my online shop (gabrielgarbowart.com/shop). Use the clickable link in my profile.

The mailing list is the best way to get first looks at new artwork, special offers, and behind the scenes updates. One email every month or two.
.
If you absolutely hate email, you can still use the code 2DAY2023 for 15% all purchases Nov 18th & 19th.

8x10” Print Available for a limited time.
.
Order your print of “Silent Reflection II” through Nov 30th.
Visit www.gabrielgarbowart.com - use the active link in my profile.
.
Prints will ship the first week of December for holiday deliveries. Take advantage of the 2-day sale Nov 18 & 19 for 15% off using discount code 2DAY2023. Makes a great gift for the art lovers on your list.

“Sweetbriar” 18x22” watercolor on paper by Gabriel Garbow, 2023.  Sold.
.
I can’t be happier with the way this quasi-commission turned out. It’s so serene and light, with plenty of details to keep the interest. It was a long time coming, this watercolor having been started just before my stay in Mexico in August, and finally reaching completion in early November after an initial abandoned attempt.
From Minnesota; living in California with my husband and corgi.
